featured.text: Baseball, on the other hand, seems more mental, like chess, and 27 those fans that prefer a quieter, more complicated game.
College education is far more complicated than ___(23)___

definition.zh_def: 複雜的，難以理解或處理的。
definition.en_def: Consisting of many interconnected parts; not easy to analyze or understand.
definition.example: The instructions for assembling the furniture were too complicated for me to follow.
